 BuildDropDown←{
     ⍝ A Dropdown is just a menu
     ⍝ displayed as a button, usually in a toolbar.
     ⍝ We can use the Menu.NewDropDown 'this-foo' to instantiate it.
     ⍝ should not need the extra level
     NewMenu←##.Main.Menu.New
     NewItem←##.Main.Menu.NewItem
     m←NewMenu''
     ⍝ s←m NewMenu⊂'Dropdown'
     i←m NewItem'Option 1' 'Ctrl+O' 'OnDropDownOp1'
     i←m NewItem'Option 2' 'Ctrl+S' 'OnDropDownOp2'
     i←m NewItem'Option 3' 'Ctrl+A' 'OnDropDownOp3'
     m
 }
